description: 
globs: **/*.java
alwaysApply: true
---
- Document all public classes, methods, and fields with JavaDoc comments
- Include @param, @return, and @throws tags in method JavaDocs when applicable
- Document API endpoints with Springdoc OpenAPI annotations
- Use @Operation to describe API operations
- Include @ApiResponse annotations to document possible responses
- Document request/response DTOs with appropriate descriptions
- Maintain a comprehensive README.md file with setup and usage instructions
- Include example API requests and responses in documentation
- Document configuration properties with @ConfigurationProperties
- Include package-info.java files for package-level documentation
- Use meaningful commit messages that describe changes
- Maintain a CHANGELOG.md file for version history
- Document database schema changes in migration scripts
- Keep documentation up-to-date with code changes